replies.body:
>Morellos is simply an overloaded item

*proceeds to put 3 passives on new item*

{{sticker:sg-lux-2}}

> [{quoted}](name=redniwediS,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=ZRjjEgWL,comment-id=0004,timestamp=2017-12-07T18:01:46.811+0000)
>
> To be fair it really only has two passives.  The CDR was made into a unique passive to stop people from stacking it.
> 
> I like the idea of your suggested item, but I have to ask what made you put a small amount of magic penetration on it?
> 
> Also part of why Morello only applies grievous wounds at low health is because of the 8 second duration.  If an AP item is going to be made that can apply it at any level of health I think the duration is going to have to match it&#x27;s AD counterpart.  That should make it better for spammy champions who can reapply it often, where as Morello would stay the better option for burst.
> 
> On top of that maybe it needs two different grievous wounds durations, one for single target spells and a shorter one for AoE?

Count how many AD penetration items there are:

1. {{item:3134}} 
2. {{item:3035}} 
3. {{item:3142}} 
4. {{item:3147}}
5. {{item:3814}} 
6. {{item:3071}} 
7. {{item:3033}} 
8. {{item:3036}}

How many AP penetration items are there?

1. {{item:3020}}
2. {{item:3136}} 
3. {{item:3151}} 
4. {{item:3135}}

Hopefully you see why I think it needs to have some penetration. Keep in mind, Magic Resist and Armor items are actually pretty close to even in numbers, yet there are far more armor penetration items than magic penetration items. 

AD has a pretty unfair advantage because of that. AP champions have to wait on cooldowns, while AD do not because auto attacks deal physical damage.

Also, I don't think it needs any different duration, if AD champions can get 2.5 auto attacks a second and apply it with every single attack.. it shouldn't matter if a DoT can reapply it each time, there is no DoT that goes off 2.5 times a second.

Now ask the question, how much MR can tanks really get? Vs. armor?

{{item:3065}}
 {{item:3193}} 
{{item:3194}}
 {{item:3001}}
 {{item:3190}} 
{{item:3060}} 
{{item:3222}} 

Now, how many of those to tanks generally build? One, a majority of the time. 2 if they build stoneplate/locket.

Now armor

{{item:3190}} 
{{item:3193}}
 {{item:3800}}
 {{item:3110}}
 {{item:3068}}
 {{item:3075}}
 {{item:3143}}
 {{item:3742}}
 {{item:3109}} 

Now, how many of these to tanks generally build? Probably 2 or 3, ignoring any cross over from stoneplate/locket. Of course dont forget {{item:3047}}  because those are the only tank boots worth shit because tenacity sucks. So thats an extra armor items in most builds.

Mages have less pen because they need less pen due to overall itemization. Champions survive magic damage through a dash of MR, and their large health pool (for tanks), rather than a large amount of MR and average health pool.
